'''''After I'm Gone''''' is a book written by [[Laura Lippman]]<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=yLfqAgAAQBAJ&source=gbs_navlinks_s|title=After I'm Gone|last=Lippman|first=Laura|date=March 4, 2014|publisher=Faber & Faber|isbn=9780571299690|language=en|access-date=March 27, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.lauralippman.net/after-im-gone-1/|title=After I'm Gone|website=LAURA LIPPMAN|language=en-US|access-date=March 27, 2017}}</ref> and published by [[William Morrow Publishers]] (an imprint of [[HarperCollins]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.harpercollins.com/9780062083395/after-im-gone|title=After I'm Gone – Laura Lippman – Hardcover|last=Lippman|first=Laura|website=HarperCollins US|language=en|access-date=March 27, 2017}}</ref>) on February 11, 2014; it won the [[Anthony Award]] for Best Novel in 2015.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.bouchercon.com/anthony-awards/winners-and-nominees/|title=Winners and Nominees|date=August 10, 2015|work=Bouchercon|access-date=March 27, 2017|language=en}}</ref>
